.\" {{ .project }} - {{ .description }}
.TH SHLIB 7 "{{ .date }}" "{{ .project }} {{ .version }}" "Bash Library"
.SH NAME
{{ .project }} \- {{ .description }}
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B source
.I /path/to/shlib.bash
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B {{ .project }}
is a library of reusable Bash functions that can be sourced into shell scripts.
It provides common utilities for arrays, strings, logging, ANSI colors,
key\-value stores, and other frequently needed operations.
.PP
The library is distributed as a single file
.RB ( shlib.bash )
for easy download and sourcing.
It is pure Bash with no external binary dependencies wherever possible.
.PP
All functions are namespaced with the
.B shlib::
prefix, and all global variables are namespaced with the
.B SHLIB_
prefix, to avoid polluting the caller's environment.
.PP
The library enables strict mode
.RB ( "set \-euo pipefail" )
when sourced.
It includes double\-source protection via the
.B SHLIB_LOADED
variable to prevent loading multiple times.
.SH REQUIREMENTS
.B {{ .project }}
requires Bash version 3 or higher.
The key\-value (KV) section requires Bash version 4 or higher
for associative array support.
The library will fail to load with an error message
if sourced in an older version of Bash.
